Package cams.enquiry

Class EnquirerUI

java.lang.Object
cams.enquiry.EnquirerUI
All Implemented Interfaces:
DashboardState, PosterUI, PostViewerUI
public class EnquirerUI
extends java.lang.Object
implements PosterUI
Class representing the user interface for enquiry operations. This class provides the template for enquiry related actions such as submitting, editing, and deleting enquiries. It extends EnquirerUI and provides the implementation for the reply method in PosterUI.

    • submitEnquiry

      protected void submitEnquiry​(User user)
      Handles the submission of a new enquiry from a user.

      This method prompts the user for the name of the camp they are enquiring about and the content of their enquiry. It also checks if the user is a committee member trying to enquire about their own camp, which is not allowed.

      Parameters:
      user - The user submitting the enquiry.

    • deleteEnquiry

      protected void deleteEnquiry​(User user, int numEnquiries)
      Handles the deletion of an existing enquiry.

      The user is prompted to select the index of the enquiry they wish to delete.

      Parameters:
      user - The user who owns the enquiry.
      numEnquiries - The total number of enquiries the user has.

    • editEnquiry

      protected void editEnquiry​(User user, int numEnquiries)
      Handles editing an existing enquiry.

      The user is prompted to select the index of the enquiry they wish to edit and provide the new content.

      Parameters:
      user - The user who owns the enquiry.
      numEnquiries - The total number of enquiries the user has.
